### Example systemd EnvironmentFile usage

# Create `/etc/vendora/env` (root-owned) and set permissions so only root can read it
# Place sensitive values here and make them readable by systemd when starting the service.

# Example file contents (DO NOT COMMIT):
SECRET_KEY=replace-me
DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@db-host:5432/vendora?sslmode=require
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0
SENTRY_DSN=
EMAIL_HOST=
EMAIL_HOST_USER=
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=

# Systemd unit snippet to load it:
# [Service]
# EnvironmentFile=/etc/vendora/env